we said git is "DISTRIBUTED" system.
we have multiple repositories (each developer has own local repository)
so they are not depended on central server, and they can develop offline!

but we collaborate on some centralized server,                                                       +------------+
instead each local repository collaborate directly!                                  +----------+    | Center DB  |      +-----------+
because it will be so complex and error prone!                                       | local DB  |<->+------------+ <--->| local DB  |
we call this "CENTRALIZED WORKFLOW"                                                  +----------+            ^           +-----------+
                                                                                                             |
                                                                                                             v
Note: the servers are distributed,                                                                     +------------+
      the workflow is centralized!                                                                     | local DB   |
                                                                                                       +------------+
Note: the advantage of this is (compare to centralized version control systems)
      we don't have single point of failure,
      if the centralized server is not accessible for period of time
      we can synchronize our work directly (with other repositories)

Note: this central repository
      can be on a private server
      can be on  git hosting services (like github,gitlab,bitbucket,...)


CLOSED-SOURCE PROJECT
all closed-source projects like private teams in companies
use "CENTRALIZED WORKFLOW" .



OPEN-SOURCE PROJECT
in open sourced projects, we have "INTEGRATION-MANAGER" work flow!
it's because every one should not change the real project directly.
they can not "PUSH" what ever they want!
the manager should permit the changes!

every developer should "FORK" repository as a copy of project on central server (github)
then "CLONE" the project from that "FORK" to local repository.
then "PUSH" them changes on "FORK"
then send "PULL REQUEST" to "MAINTAINER" of the project,
he see our notif and will pull our changes from our "FORK"
then if he agree, he will merge on his local repository
and finally push them on the "OFFICIAL REPOSITORY"

Note: FORK is copy of official repository on github (not local repository)
      so we can change it!
